<tr id="L159"><td><a href="#L159">159</a></td><td>APOLLO:  No, you do not, Captain. They are mine. To save, to cherish, or to destroy at my will.</td></tr>

<tr id="L160"><td><a href="#L160">160</a></td><td>CAROLYN:  But why? What you've said so far makes no sense at all.</td></tr>

<tr id="L161"><td><a href="#L161">161</a></td><td>APOLLO:  How like Aphrodite and Athena. The beauty, grace. And you seem wise for a woman. What is your name?</td></tr>

